    About this item

    • HERE COMES THE BASS: Pronounced beats, stronger vibes. These wireless on-ear headphones have a BASS boost button for deep bass at the touch of a button. Powerful 32mm drivers bring out the best in your favourite tracks. Experience like never before!
    • ANYTIME, ANYWHERE: Get 29 hours of playtime from over 600 songs or soundtrack several long-haul flights with just a 2-hour charge via USB-C. When you need a little more juice, a 15-minute charge gives you an extra 8 hours.
    • DESIGNED FOR COMFORT: These 150g on-ear headphones are the ultimate in comfort! The cushioned headband is so light you can barely feel it, while the soft ear cups are clearly marked for left/right ears and can be angled until they feel just right.
    • AT YOUR FINGERTIPS: One press of the multi-function button lets you answer calls, pause music and wake your voice assistant and more. These headphones are ready to pair as soon as you turn them on.
    • DESIGNED FOR PORTABILITY: The ear cups fold flat and swivel inwards to fit easily in your pocket or bag, making them ideal for travelling, studying or working. The matte colour is the perfect finishing touch to your everyday look.

    Quality about the Details

    Cushioned, Adjustable Headband

    These on-ear headphones have a padded headband that's so light you can barely feel it. The length of the headband can be adjusted to fit your head.

    Breathable Ear Cushions

    Featured with breathable ear cushions, PHILIPS headphones keep your ears stay comfortable, even during extended listening sessions. The soft ear cups are clearly marked for left or right ears, and you can angle them until they feel just right.

    Compact Foldable Design

    These ear cups are just the best! They fold flat and swivel inwards, so you can easily store them in your pocket or bag. Just fold them up when you're ready to go! They're perfect for travelling and enjoying music wherever you go.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    • Amazoneddy
      4.0 out of 5 stars Decent for casual use, good battery life & audio. But can be a bit fragile on the hinges
      Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2025
      Color: Matte BlackVerified Purchase
      Here's the bottom line - a decent pick for the price, sound quality is good, battery life is good, but durability is a question.

      Here’s how I’d sum up my real-world experience with the PHILIPS H4205 Wireless On-Ear Headphones (Black) after using them for a few weeks:

      I was initially drawn in by the specs and the price. In daily use, they mostly deliver — the lightweight frame (per the listing) is comfy and easy to wear for long stretches without a lot of pressure on the head or ears. The ear cups are softly padded and swivel, which helps with fit and portability. BUT ... I also round that the swivel on the ear cups were a weak point in the design.

      On sound: the 32 mm drivers give surprisingly full audio for this class, and the BASS boost adds an extra punch. Without bass mode they’re balanced enough for podcasts or general listening, though I noticed that in more complex pieces or treble-rich tracks there were moments where detail got a little muddled. In other words, they are more than good enough for casual use. Battery-wise, I got close to the claimed 29 hours on lighter usage, cool. The fast-charging is also nice — 15 minutes of charge giving you a few more hours is very handy.

      Now the downside. The build feels a bit plastic and lightweight, which is a double-edged sword. It’s easy to carry, but long-term durability is questionable. The ear pads are quick to come off, and pain to get back on. The hinges on the ear cups are the weak point in the design, like I said earlier. They broke after a few weeks of use (I feel asleep wearing them, and I guess the weight of my head onto the pillow or whatever was enough to break them.

      Still, I'm giving them relatively high scores for the price point ... as long as you don't fall asleep on them, sit on them or whatever ..

Budgeting in an extra $20 and going for a different brand will pay off to spare the frustration alone.

    About this Item

    • HERE COMES THE BASS: Pronounced beats, stronger vibes. These wireless on-ear headphones have a BASS boost button for deep bass at the touch of a button. Powerful 32mm drivers bring out the best in your favourite tracks. Experience like never before!
    • ANYTIME, ANYWHERE: Get 29 hours of playtime from over 600 songs or soundtrack several long-haul flights with just a 2-hour charge via USB-C. When you need a little more juice, a 15-minute charge gives you an extra 8 hours.
    • DESIGNED FOR COMFORT: These 150g on-ear headphones are the ultimate in comfort! The cushioned headband is so light you can barely feel it, while the soft ear cups are clearly marked for left/right ears and can be angled until they feel just right.
    • AT YOUR FINGERTIPS: One press of the multi-function button lets you answer calls, pause music and wake your voice assistant and more. These headphones are ready to pair as soon as you turn them on.
    • DESIGNED FOR PORTABILITY: The ear cups fold flat and swivel inwards to fit easily in your pocket or bag, making them ideal for travelling, studying or working. The matte colour is the perfect finishing touch to your everyday look.

    Product Description

    Get rolling with Philips H4205 On-Ear Wireless Headphones. One press of the BASS boost button sends deep impactful notes thundering through your ears. Thanks to 32mm drivers, you get rich, detailed sound and crystal clear calls. Adjust volume, take calls, and command your voice assistant by pressing the multifunction button on the ear cups. The cushioned headband is light and adjustable, so you barely feel any pressure on your ears. With 29 hours of playtime, you get to pore through every one of your bass-heavy playlists, and a quick 15-minute boost will give you another 4 hours. The ear cups fold flat and swivel inward, so you can easily fit it in your pocket or handbag. Choose from four matte colors to stand out from the crowd.
